Kâty. VI, 6, 4 leaves it doubtful; but the commentator interprets the
rule as referring to the Adhvaryu and Sacrificer, in accordance with the
reading of the Kâ*n*va text--'atha yâ*h* pari*s*ish*t*â âpo bhavanti
tâbhir adhvaryu*s* *k*a ya*g*amâna*s* *k*ânushi*ñk*ata*h*.'

<span id="fn_477"></span>[192:2](sbe2632.htm#fr_479.md) Âsthâpayanti =
